{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_77","type":"agent_message","text":"`DataStructures` is still metadata-shaped too. Its static initializer reflectively does `ClassLoader.loadClass(\"java.util.concurrent.LinkedTransferQueue\")` followed by `Class.newInstance()`, and if that reflective constructor call fails it silently swallows the exception and leaves `LTQclass` null, which matches the observed `NullPointerException`. I’m registering the zero-arg constructor for `java.util.concurrent.LinkedTransferQueue` under the same Jersey entry condition and rerunning the targeted test."}}
